          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">For donors</h3>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-3">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-fuchsia-400">Step 1</div>
            <div class="mt-1 font-medium">Click the donate button</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Find a Paylink button on a publisher's site and click it to start a donation.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-fuchsia-400">Step 2</div>
            <div class="mt-1 font-medium">Get a fresh address</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Optionally enter an amount and description. A unique subaddress and QR code are generated just for you.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
            <div class="text-sm font-medium text-fuchsia-400">Step 3</div>
            <div class="mt-1 font-medium">Send from your wallet</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Scan the QR or copy the address into your Monero wallet app (Monerujo, Cake Wallet, etc.) and send.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PRIVACY -->
    <section id="privacy" class="mt-24 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Privacy by design
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-zinc-400 sm:text-lg">
        Paylinks is built to minimize data exposure for both publishers and donors.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">No spend key</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            We only use your private view key to derive subaddresses. We can't spend your funds — ever.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">No payment logging</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            We don't log donor IPs, amounts, descriptions, or timestamps. Payment metadata exists only in the donor's browser.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Fresh address per request</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            Each donor gets a unique subaddress. No single address links all your supporters together.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Donor isolation</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            If one donor is coerced into revealing their transaction, they can't expose other donors — each received a different address.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-6">
        <a
          href="/docs/paylinks/privacy"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 hover:text-white"
        >
          Read the full privacy documentation
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/docs/paylinks/infrastructure"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 hover:text-white"
        >
          Infrastructure & data security
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CLEARNET & TOR -->
    <section id="tor" class="mt-24 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Clearnet & Tor separation
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-zinc-400 sm:text-lg">
        Paylinks runs separate services for clearnet and Tor. This is a security feature, not a limitation.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">No cross-origin requests</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            The clearnet site only talks to the clearnet API. The onion site only talks to the onion API. No mixing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Traffic isolation</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            Tor traffic stays within Tor. No exit nodes, no clearnet exposure — your activity remains within the onion network.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Independent infrastructure</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            Clearnet and onion services run on separate infrastructure. If one is compromised, the other continues independently.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Create where you publish</div>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
            Want a donate button for your clearnet site? Create it here. For your onion site? Use the onion version of Paylinks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-6">
        <a
          href="/docs/paylinks/tor-separation"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 hover:text-white"
        >
          Why separate services?
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a
          href="/docs/onion-services"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 hover:text-white"
        >
          About Anonomi onion services
          <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DISTINCTION -->
    <section id="distinction" class="mt-24 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/[0.04] p-6 sm:p-8">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Paylinks vs. Messenger Payment Requests</h3>

        <p class="mt-3 text-zinc-400">
          Anonomi has two ways to handle Monero payments — use the right one for your situation.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
            <div class="font-medium text-fuchsia-400">Paylinks</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Public donation buttons for websites and blogs. Address generation happens server-side using your view key.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">Best for: Publishers receiving donations from unknown supporters.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4">
            <div class="font-medium text-zinc-300">Messenger Payment Requests</div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">
              Private peer-to-peer payments inside encrypted conversations. Address generation happens client-side in your wallet.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-xs text-zinc-500">Best for: Trusted contacts exchanging payments privately.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6">
          <a
            href="/messenger#tab-payments"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-zinc-300 hover:text-white"
          >
            Learn about Messenger Payment Requests
            <span aria-hidden="true">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- GET STARTED -->
    <section id="get-started" class="mt-24 scroll-mt-24">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
        Get started
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base text-zinc-400 sm:text-lg">
        Create a Paylink in under a minute. You'll need your Monero primary address and private view key.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-6">
